	('B3gElfMJpv6UpaQQIwfr9', 'Wrath of Junshi ', 'https://utfs.io/f/e836f3e9-ab32-44b8-8604-89bca2c1e7e9-y5fez3.webp', '<p>When Seichi began, each established group of settlers were blessed from the great Kami, the benevolent gods of our world. Shine was blessed with Amaterasu, the goddess of the sun.” Shroud was blessed with Susanoo, the ruler of storms and the ocean. Silence worshipped Tsukuyomi, the moon Kami. Konoki worshipped Kitsune, and eventually the two became Tsukimori, adopting both Kami, Kitsune and Tsukuyomi. Current appeased their Kami, Fujin. Glacier was blessed with Kuraokami. Each village represented its Kami, and their respective gods watched over them peacefully.</p>\n\n<p>However, one Kami watched in envy. The Kami Junshi, the Kami of provocation watched as the other Kami embraced their people and villages and helped them flourish. Junshi was Angry that no village had shown him reverence. No offerings to Junshi. No temples for worship. He watched as the beginning times of Seichi came to a close, and the first ninja villages were evolved from the initial settling of humans all over the globe. When the first era began, Junshi knew what he would do.</p> \n\nHe decided he would use his powers for revenge. \n\n<p>Sweeping throughout the lands of Seichi, he used his Godlike powers to infect settlers all over, causing them to fight amongst one another, rob and steal, and in some cases even take their own lives. This catastrophe continued, and as it grew lands were set ablaze, livestock were burned alive, crops were destroyed and many people went missing.</p>\n\n<p>The first ninja of this era were forced to ban together, and with the help of The Kage, the first leaders of this time, they were able to seal Junshi with the now ancient sealing scroll: Ten Fu Chēn. (Heavenly Sealing Chains) \n\nAfter Using this forbidden technique, the Kage sealed away the scroll and left its whereabouts only to the Village Elders, as a power to tame a god should not be used lightly.</p>\n\n<p>Now, many years later, Junshi has returned. As the seal wore down with time, Junshi plotted his escape, and broke free. Rising sbove all of Seichi he has declared war on every village:</p>\n\n<i> <p>“The Kami of this world are weak. Embracing humanity has only shown me that compassion is weakness. I will destroy this world, or become its ruler. Worship me, or face my wrath!”</i> </p>\n\n<p>Junshi loomed down upon Seichi, and with a wave of his hand, spread a fog of hysteria on Seichi. People once again began robbing, fighting and destroying their villages. If left unchecked, Junshi would destroy this world.</p>\n\n\n<p><i>“Please help us find the ancient forbidden sealing scroll to send Junshi away for another thousand years. The people of Seichi need you!\nEach Village holds a Riddle to uncover the location of Ten Fu Chēn. Please visit them to help Banish Junshi once more! We have uncovered the first riddle for you!”</p></i>\n', '<i>“Unbelievable! You actually managed to obtain the ancient scroll! Even though Junshi got away, we now have a weapon against him when he returns. Thank you for aiding the citizens of Seichi. Please accept this as a reward!”</i>', 'D', 1, NULL, 'all_time', 'event', '{\"reward\": {\"reward_exp\": 1000, \"reward_rank\": \"NONE\", \"reward_items\": [], \"reward_money\": 25000, \"reward_badges\": [], \"reward_jutsus\": [], \"reward_tokens\": 100, \"reward_prestige\": 200, \"reward_clanpoints\": 100}, \"objectives\": [{\"id\": \"KobuvMzt7IolOSrhDMi12\", \"task\": \"collect_item\", \"image\": \"https://utfs.io/f/4fcf2972-6499-4289-aa04-76af3f1ffd7c-1fztx.webp\", \"sector\": 222, \"latitude\": 5, \"attackers\": [], \"completed\": 0, \"item_name\": \"Scroll 1\", \"longitude\": 2, \"reward_exp\": 0, \"description\": \"Receive the first riddle from wake island\", \"reward_rank\": \"NONE\", \"hideLocation\": false, \"reward_items\": [], \"reward_money\": 0, \"reward_badges\": [], \"reward_jutsus\": [], \"reward_tokens\": 0, \"colle