	('wMl1KGZeXPLw9QMhaDJT5', 'The Path to Glacier', 'https://utfs.io/f/093203f4-204b-4367-a3cc-cb58a9a66107-keq49e.webp', 'Welcome, traveler, to the village of Glacier, where the unyielding spirit of its people met the icy challenge of Kuraokami. The history here is one of endurance and mastery over the elements. To truly understand the essence of Glacier, you must trace the steps of the first settlers, from their arrival in the Hyuogaan Mountains to their encounters with the kami of ice and snow. Join me in uncovering the story of this remarkable place.<br><br>\n\nStart your journey at the entrance of the Hyuogaan Mountains, where the brave settlers first arrived and faced the harsh, icy conditions.<br><br>\n\nDelve into the deeper parts of the Hyuogaan Mountains, where the settlers encountered the enchanting yet dangerous Yuki Onna, a beautiful yet dangerous spirit. Despite her enchanting presence, the settlers managed to escape her grasp, continuing their journey.<br><br>\n\nContinue to the Hyuogaan Icesheet, where Glacier is located today. This is where the settlers encountered Kuraokami and faced his icy challenge.<br><br>\n\nNext, make your way to the Frozen Highlands, a region known for its spectacular views and harsh climate. The settlers consolidated their strength and built advanced structures here.<br><br>\n\nFinally, venture into Tornado Valley, a region with a special connection to Glacier. This place holds secrets and mysteries deeply tied to Glacier\'s history, but those are stories for another day.\n', 'Congratulations, traveler! You’ve completed your journey in Glacier, exploring its rich history. Starting at the Hyuogaan Mountains, you traced the settlers’ first steps. You delved into the depths, escaping the Yuki Onna, and faced Kuraokami’s icy challenge in the Icesheet. In the Frozen Highlands, you saw their advanced structures, and in Tornado Valley, you uncovered its deep ties to Glacier’s mysteries. Well done! — Tenjiro Sensei', 'D', 1, NULL, 'a